<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>About</title>

  <style>
    body {
      font-family: "Bradley Hand", cursive;
      background: #fff8d6; /* warm yellow */
      color: #1a4b8c;      /* ink blue */
      padding: 2rem;
      line-height: 1.6;
      max-width: 650px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      color: #1a4b8c;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }

    /* Neutral sticky-note style back link */
    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #fffef7;
      padding: 0.6rem 1rem;
      border: 1px solid #e0dfd8;
      box-shadow: 2px 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
      transform: rotate(-1deg);
      font-family: "Bradley Hand", cursive;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #222;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>

  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>
    Seasonal Notes is a small, quiet experiment in noticing.  
    Instead of building a traditional website with tidy pages and rigid structure,
    this project gathers fragments — small seasonal impressions — and scatters them
    across a single canvas.
  </p>

  <p>
    The notes are intentionally messy, a little crooked, like sticky notes pinned
    to a wall or scribbles left on a desk. They aren’t meant to stand alone as
    pages. They belong together, side by side, forming a loose collage of the year.
  </p>

  <p>
    This page exists only to explain the intention behind the form — a companion
    note to the main piece.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a class="back-link" href="../index.html">Back to Seasonal Notes</a>
  </p>

</body>
</html>
